BIB                  8         22
TITLE      Measurement of the fission cross section of the 235U
           isomer by thermal neutrons
AUTHOR     (V.I.Mostovoi,G.I.Ustroev)
REFERENCE  (J,SJA,57,692,1984) Engl.translation of J,AE .
           #doi:10.1007/BF01123638
           (J,AE,57,241,198410) Issue 4.
           ((S,INDC(CCP)-235,(1),295,1984)=
           (C,83KIEV,1,295,1983))
INSTITUTE  (4RUSKUR)
FACILITY   (REAC,4RUSKUR) Reactor F-1
DETECTOR   (SOLST) Semiconductor breakdown detector.
            FF registration efficiency was defined by Cf-252
            calibration.
CORRECTION  Background from backing and detector ( 0.98 1/min;
            6-12 % of the total count ) was subtracted.
HISTORY    (19850114C)
           (20110718A) M.M. Upper -> lower case correction.
           Dates were corrected for 4-digits year.
           BIB information was added.
           Ref. J,SJA was added.
           (20251006A) Ref. S,INDC(CCP)-235 was added.
           STATUS was corrected for new rules.
ENDBIB              22
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           25
SUBENT        40834002   20251006   20260319   20260319       4226
BIB                  7         16
REACTION   ((92-U-235-M(N,F),,SIG,,SPA)/(92-U-235(N,F),,SIG,,SPA))
INC-SPECT    Thermal reactor spectrum, spectrum temperature
             360 degree Kelvin.
             Thermal neutron flux 0.7E+10 /(cm**2*sec).
SAMPLE      U-235-M (1/2+, 76.8 eV) sample was produced via alpha
           decay of Pu-239. ~ 10 ng, area 0.2 cm2.
            Pu-239 monitor sample.
            Number of nuclei was calculated from alpha-spectra
            measurement.
DECAY-DATA (92-U-235-M,26.MIN)
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) Type of uncertainty is not explained in the
           article.
STATUS     (TABLE,,V.I.Mostovoi+,J,SJA,57,692,1984)
            Text, page 693.
HISTORY    (20251006U) "PART-DET   (FF)" was deleted according to
           a comment of N.Otsuka (NDS,IAEA)
